column5: Niiiiiiiice!... man I cant wait for the dog days of summer!! Thanks for sharing!  Ger.
....doesnt it though? Nungesser Lake- 8 weeks and counting down!  Great stuff Whopper, thanks.  Wayne....
Ice is thick on Nungesser and they're still making more.
Nice pics Phil and nice eyes. Yum!
Thanks Phil, now I have the itch bad for my trip this July. I enjoyed the pics.
Very nice Phil!!  dk

Here's a few pics on our return flight to base camp after a week of fishing at Whiteclay Lake which is northwest of Armstrong        Heading into a thunderstorm at base camp, just beat the rain after off loading gear.  Some pics of fish from the trip     Sat and watched a cow moose and her baby feed in the water one morning    Yes I have cabin fever  Whopper
Great pics Philbo!!!... and those look like some very nice fish too!!!
Great shots Phil, specially the moose pics.  Looks like a gorgeous area to spend a few weeks.
NICEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE
Great shots to help jump start me on a cooler than usual day.  Did those dark gold walleyes come from deep water?
You made my day I just took out the snowblower  we got 25cm of snow today and I also have cabin fever.I need to go out in my boat.One more Month

Cool! I've got fond memories of Whiteclay and that very camp. When soloing through there a few years back a group of guys from Ohio staying at that outpost befriended me and invited me over for a steak dinner and some cold beers Good times, they were a great bunch of guys.
nice shots phil. Thanks for sharing.

Thanks TG, most of the walleyes caught that week were in depths from 10 to 25 feet. Some were gold and some were silver and black or green and black, if you notice the one pic I have blue residue on my white tshirt from a few that were caught. That pike had been harassing my buddy and bit him off twice fishing for eyes before I put the whammy on him.  Wasn't a big fish but I called him and my bud couldn't believe it.  Lew they could drop me off and leave me there for a whole summer and it wouldn't bother me one bit.  Oh by the way this is one of the lakes that solepaddler has went through on at least one of his journeys.  Whopper  sorry solo you were replying while I was typing
Thanks Phil...always a great day when I see a Beaver....let alone get into one.
Nice Dor√© and Brochet.
Man' I've seen two yellow beavers in the last week, must be mating season.  Nice pics.
Beauty pics Phil. Thanks for sharing.
awesome pics Phil!!!! just made it 5 degrees colder
Great shots Phil!
Mod Alert!  Well said Wayne!
What ever do you mean Dax....
Beautiful pics.....and some nice fish too!!  Jason
Great pics Phil.
Very Nice!!! Looks like a great trip! Thanks for the post!
Great pics Whopper. I've did a one-day fly-in several years back.  I'd love to do that again ... even try a week-long trip.

Great stuff Phil, thanks for posting that. Now I can't wait for the 3rd weekend in May, but I still have some ice fishing left, and a few steelhead trips, maybe an ice out(or still in) speck fishing trip to last me until then.
Looks like an great trip. Amazing photos thanks for sharing.
Right On Whop.  That gets a mans urges for summer sun and backwoods walleye flowing.
Thanks for the pictures.
